# Whitelist: ignore everything, then un-ignore only what the Dockerfile COPYs
# (vendor/, cozy-module/, docker-files/). A new sibling dir (todo/, design/,
# docs.docker.com/, …) is then excluded from the build context automatically —
# no .dockerignore edit needed. If a future COPY needs another path, the build
# fails loud ("file not found") rather than silently re-bloating the context.
*
!vendor/
!cozy-module/
!docker-files/
